description._content: Description: The new H.C. Sir John Le Rougetel Visits Swaziland. Right to Left R.C. Colonel Van Oudtshoorn C. of P. P.C. H.C. & Mr Sukati A.S. Location: Swaziland Date: 1951 Description: Mr Fitzpatrick S.For A.A Talking with the P.C. Also In the Group Are Mr Stebbing G.S., Mr Fannin D.D Mbabane, Mr Armstrong F.A.S. & Mrs Morgan. Location: Mbabane, Swaziland Date: 1951 Description: The H.C., Watching Trade School Apprentices at Work. Left to Right Mr Aldridge, Principal, H.C., Mr Fairlie P.S. to H.C., R.C., & Mr Pitcher P.E.O. Location: Swaziland Date: 1951 Description: The H.C. Being Introduced to Swaziland Government officials In Mbabane. Location: Mbabane, Swaziland Date: 1951 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/229 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives, uploaded as part of the Africa Through a Lens project.
